📅 Delhi University Academic Calendar 2025–26 Released
The University of Delhi has officially announced the academic schedule for all Undergraduate and Postgraduate programmes for the session 2025–26. Key dates include:
	•	Semester I/III/V/VII begins: 1st August 2025
	•	Autumn Break: 19th–26th October 2025
	•	Theory Exams: From 10th December 2025
	•	Winter Break: 28th Dec 2025 – 1st Jan 2026

Semester II/IV/VI/VIII begins: 2nd January 2026,
with summer vacation scheduled from 1st June – 20th July 2026.

The summer break for the 2024–25 session is also extended till 31st July 2025.

📍Issued on: 4th July 2025
🖊️ By the Registrar, University of Delhi

🎉 Proud Moment for the University of Delhi! 🎉

We are delighted to announce that the University of Delhi has once again secured Rank 328 in the QS World University Rankings 2026, firmly maintaining its position among the top global institutions. 🏛️

More significantly, DU has emerged as the top public university in India, showcasing outstanding performance across several critical indicators:
✅ #1 among Indian institutions in Employment Outcomes – reflecting the strong employability and career readiness of our graduates.
✅ Notable improvement in Research Performance – driven by impactful publications and increased citations across disciplines.
✅ Stronger International Collaboration – marking DU’s growing presence and partnerships on the global academic stage.

This achievement is a reflection of the collective dedication and pursuit of excellence by our faculty, students, researchers, and alumni. We are proud to represent India on the global academic map and will continue to strive for even greater heights. 🚀

University of Delhi Foundation
